commit.message: Fix __signature__ support if object has a __file__

Explicitly set README content type

The README, being a reStructuredText document, is not rendered as such on PyPI, just as plaintext.

This *should* fix that.

Require Sphinx < 7 for now

Removal of the setuptools integration from Sphinx breaks our builds. See
https://github.com/sphinx-doc/sphinx/pull/11363 for the change in
Sphinx.
Bit too heavy handed on the translations.
Refer directly to the top-level package in docs.

Clarify fork instructions in contributing docs

`setup.py` expects to be able to find git tags in order to properly set
the package version. If a fork does not have any tags, `pip install -e
.` will fail due to the default `"unknown"` being an invalid version.
Fix URL typo in package metadata
